<br>
The Death Gate Cycle is a great series by them but more enjoyed if you understand the Dragonlance realm. <br>
<br>
Other than that there are some others:<br>
<br>
R.A. Salvatore's dark elf series is outstanding and an easy read. Or any of his book actually as i find him a very talented writer. This goes with understanding the Forgotten Realms tho and knowing a little background there. <br>
<br>
Thieve's World is another good series. Speaking of which if anyone has the 3rd volume id be more than happy to buy it off you or borrow it and mail it back to you after i finished it as im rereading the series and found that is the only book im lacking in my series. <br>
<br>
The Wheel of Time by Robert Jordan is another great series, although  it might not get completed as he is supposedly in bad health and might not finish the work before he dies. This would be a travesty as its such a well written series. <br>
<br>
Stephen King actually made another good series. The Dark Tower series. The only downfall on this one is that he puts out so many books he neglects to finish this one series. It is quite facinating tho even tho he is more well known as a &quot;horror&quot; author. <br>
<br>
Another great set that is completed is The Guardian Flame series by Joel Rosenberg. This is more for the old pen and paper type of people as it actually is based on people that played the game D&amp;D and were drawn into the world of fantasy. If you can find it it was actually worth the read. <br>
<br>
I have many more that I will add later but those should get you started on some good reading and keep you busy for a while<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liviusmaximus>LiviusMaximus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>SotE - GL</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/8/03 2:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good Medieval Fantasy series</span><hr size=1> I agree Lenwaen, the Feist books are excellent.<br>
